The arcade mode will help you play the game without prior experience by automatically leveling the plane everytime, but on the contrary it mades the plane maneuvering janky and wobbly because you try to turn and the control mode force plane to level. 

The classic mode however doesnt automatically level your plane but its gave you the freedom of movements and  allow you to maneuver smoothly, but it needs some get used to.

I recommend you try the classic mode gura, it does need some training but it gives you the potential of doing crazy maneuver.

LS is for maneuvering, drag down will pitch up, drag left and right to roll.
RS is for aiming, drag down will pitch down, drag left and right to yaw.
Free look camera is not a thing in PW
